HEADWORD: Qualmish
<hw>Qualm"ish</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Sick at the stomach; affected
with nausea or sickly languor; inclined to vomit.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Qualm"ish*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Qualm"ish*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Quamash</ent>⟦br⟧
